reagent-name-teriparatide = teriparatide
reagent-desc-teriparatide = A chemical compound that binds to bone tissue and crystallizes at low temperatures, repairing fractures in the process. Prolonged exposure is mildly toxic.
reagent-name-cordrazine = cordrazine
reagent-desc-cordrazine = A variant of tricordrazine that is used to stabilize people weakly, commonly used alongside other chemicals
reagent-name-caridine = caridine
reagent-desc-caridine = Caridine is a slower acting variant of bicaridine. Alike cordrazine, it is commonly used alongside other chemicals
